<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="220" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1150,2042]" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1294,1321]" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The combination of a broad, dorsally thickened anellus and minute ventral lobes of the uncus in the male genitalia distinguishes 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stonis &amp; Diškus &amp; Vargas" authorityYear="2019" box="[474,639,1331,1357]" class="Insecta" family="Tischeriidae" genus="Astrotischeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="colombiana">
<emphasis box="[474,639,1331,1357]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">A. colombiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from all known 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Puplesis &amp; Diskus. Based" authorityYear="2003" box="[833,991,1331,1357]" class="Insecta" family="Tischeriidae" genus="Astrotischeria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[833,991,1331,1357]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Astrotischeria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species. The unique morphology of its phallus also makes this species very distinctive.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="222" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1150,2042]" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1403,1429]" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[273,409,1403,1430]" captionStart="FIGURES 20–32" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1928,1953]" captionTargetBox="[171,1426,221,1875]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1431,211,1890]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 20–32. Exuviae and adults of new Tischeriidae species from Colombia. 20–25, Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov., exuviae; 26, same, male adult, holotype; 27, same, paratype; 28, same, other paratype; 29–32, A. ochrimaculosa Diškus, Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov., male adult, holotype (MPUJ)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337707/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Figs. 26–28</figureCitation>
). Forewing length 3.7–4.0 mm; wingspan 8.0–8.5 mm (n = 3). Head: Face triangular, smoothly-scaled, cream; labial palpus cream to yellowish cream; frontal tuft comprised of grey, yellowish-tipped lamellar scales or sometimes entirely yellowish cream; antenna distinctly longer than half the length of forewing; flagellum dark grey, glossy; sensillae very fine, cream. Thorax: Predominantly yellowish cream, also with some scales that are basally ochre cream. Tegula and forewing speckled with black, white-tipped, and ochre scales; latter particularly common in apical half of wing forming characteristic, distinct, ochre stripes: one long, along forewing fold, and one to three short closer to anterior margin of forewing; fringe grey, at apex grey to ochre; fringe line distinct, comprised of black scales; forewing underside blackish grey, without spots or androconia. Hindwing and its fringe blackish grey on upper side and underside, without androconia, with brown frenulum and about 10 brown-black costal bristles. Legs dark grey, densely speckled with cream-tipped scales. Abdomen: Brown-black with purple and blue iridescence on upper side, predominantly yellowish cream with some irregularly scattered brown scales on underside; anal tufts blackish grey, distinctive, merged into one tuft; genital plates dark grey, distally yellowish cream. Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[269,404,1834,1861]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 33–39" captionStart-1="FIGURES 40–46" captionStart-2="FIGURES 47–53" captionStartId-0="7.[151,264,1954,1979]" captionStartId-1="8.[151,264,1929,1954]" captionStartId-2="9.[151,264,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox-0="[166,1423,226,1890]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1431,267,1828]" captionTargetBox-2="[183,1408,257,1814]" captionTargetId-0="figure@7.[151,1431,221,1898]" captionTargetId-1="figure@8.[151,1431,267,1828]" captionTargetId-2="figure@9.[151,1431,242,1824]" captionTargetPageId-0="7" captionTargetPageId-1="8" captionTargetPageId-2="9" captionText-0="FIGURES 33–39. Male genitalia of Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov., capsule with phallus removed, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD960 (MPUJ)." captionText-1="FIGURES 40–46. Male genitalia of Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov., phallus. 40–42, apical part, lateral and ventral (41) view; 43–44, general view, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD956; 45–46, same, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD960 (MPUJ)." captionText-2="FIGURES 47–53. Male genitalia of Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov. 47, 48, 50, 51, lateral view of capsule (50, with phallus little removed), paratype, genitalia slide no. AD956; 49, ventral view of uncus, genitalia slide no. AD958; 52, 53, general view of capsule with phallus, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD958 (MPUJ)." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3337709/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3337711/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/3337713/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Figs. 33–53</figureCitation>
) with capsule 
<quantity box="[568,711,1834,1861]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.425" metricValueMax="5.8" metricValueMin="5.05" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="542.5" valueMax="580.0" valueMin="505.0">505–580 µm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[782,869,1835,1861]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="220.0">220 µm</quantity>
wide. Uncus (
<figureCitation box="[1032,1167,1834,1862]" captionStart="FIGURES 33–39" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1954,1979]" captionTargetBox="[166,1423,226,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1431,221,1898]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 33–39. Male genitalia of Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov., capsule with phallus removed, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD960 (MPUJ)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337709/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Figs. 35, 36</figureCitation>
) comprised of two long dorsal lobes and two very short, pointed ventral lobes. Valva divided (
<figureCitation box="[953,1042,1871,1897]" captionStart="FIGURES 33–39" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1954,1979]" captionTargetBox="[166,1423,226,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1431,221,1898]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 33–39. Male genitalia of Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov., capsule with phallus removed, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD960 (MPUJ)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337709/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Figs 34</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1056,1131,1870,1897]" captionStart="FIGURES 47–53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[183,1408,257,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1431,242,1824]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 47–53. Male genitalia of Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov. 47, 48, 50, 51, lateral view of capsule (50, with phallus little removed), paratype, genitalia slide no. AD956; 49, ventral view of uncus, genitalia slide no. AD958; 52, 53, general view of capsule with phallus, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD958 (MPUJ)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337713/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">48, 51</figureCitation>
): ventral lobe (main body) straight, gradually narrowed towards apex, about 
<quantity box="[708,796,1906,1933]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="350.0">350 µm</quantity>
long (excluding the basal process); dorsal lobe 2.5 times shorter, inwardly curved; transtilla absent; basal process of valva long (
<figureCitation box="[946,1039,1943,1969]" captionStart="FIGURES 33–39" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1954,1979]" captionTargetBox="[166,1423,226,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1431,221,1898]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 33–39. Male genitalia of Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov., capsule with phallus removed, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD960 (MPUJ)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337709/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Figs. 37</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1051,1125,1942,1969]" captionStart="FIGURES 47–53" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1919,1944]" captionTargetBox="[183,1408,257,1814]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1431,242,1824]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 47–53. Male genitalia of Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov. 47, 48, 50, 51, lateral view of capsule (50, with phallus little removed), paratype, genitalia slide no. AD956; 49, ventral view of uncus, genitalia slide no. AD958; 52, 53, general view of capsule with phallus, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD958 (MPUJ)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337713/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">51, 52</figureCitation>
). Anellus thickened, ventral part with 3–4 setae laterally (
<figureCitation box="[484,569,1979,2005]" captionStart="FIGURES 33–39" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1954,1979]" captionTargetBox="[166,1423,226,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1431,221,1898]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 33–39. Male genitalia of Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov., capsule with phallus removed, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD960 (MPUJ)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337709/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Fig. 39</figureCitation>
), dorsal part long and wide, distally rounded (
<figureCitation box="[1095,1180,1979,2005]" captionStart="FIGURES 33–39" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1954,1979]" captionTargetBox="[166,1423,226,1890]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1431,221,1898]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 33–39. Male genitalia of Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov., capsule with phallus removed, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD960 (MPUJ)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337709/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
). Phallus 
<quantity box="[1292,1436,1978,2005]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.975" metricValueMax="6.1" metricValueMin="5.85" pageId="1" pageNumber="220" unit="mm" value="597.5" valueMax="610.0" valueMin="585.0">585–610 µm</quantity>
long, distally deeply bifurcated (
<figureCitation box="[515,652,2015,2042]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–46" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1929,1954]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,267,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1431,267,1828]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 40–46. Male genitalia of Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov., phallus. 40–42, apical part, lateral and ventral (41) view; 43–44, general view, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD956; 45–46, same, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD960 (MPUJ)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337711/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Figs. 43–46</figureCitation>
), with lateral processes and fine spines (
<figureCitation box="[1103,1241,2015,2041]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–46" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1929,1954]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,267,1828]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1431,267,1828]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 40–46. Male genitalia of Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov., phallus. 40–42, apical part, lateral and ventral (41) view; 43–44, general view, paratype, genitalia slide no. AD956; 45–46, same, holotype, genitalia slide no. AD960 (MPUJ)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337711/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="220">Figs. 40–42</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,153,647]" pageId="2" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,153,179]" pageId="2" pageNumber="221">Female.</emphasis>
Head and Thorax: Externally similar to male, but thorax and forewing pattern tend to be much paler; forewing with some brown and black-brown scales, but ochre cream scales prevail; dark ochre stripes on forewing less distinct, however still visible. Hindwing and its fringe dark grey. Abdomen: Grey-brown, glossy on upper side, yellowish cream on underside; yellowish cream anal tuft highly contrasting with surrounding grey-brown scales. Genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[271,407,296,323]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1787,1812]" captionTargetBox="[161,1416,247,1681]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1431,237,1691]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54–57. Female genitalia of Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov., paratype, genitalia slide no. AD956 (MPUJ). 54, general view; 55, 56, apophyses and ovipositor; 57, coils of ductus spermathecae (broken off)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337715/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="221">Figs. 54–56</figureCitation>
) total length about 
<quantity box="[633,739,297,323]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="2" pageNumber="221" unit="mm" value="1900.0">1900 µm</quantity>
. Ovipositor lobes small, clothed with short, stout and darker, modified setae (‘peg setae’) (
<figureCitation box="[484,569,332,359]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1787,1812]" captionTargetBox="[161,1416,247,1681]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1431,237,1691]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54–57. Female genitalia of Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov., paratype, genitalia slide no. AD956 (MPUJ). 54, general view; 55, 56, apophyses and ovipositor; 57, coils of ductus spermathecae (broken off)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337715/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="221">Fig. 55</figureCitation>
); area between ovipositor lobes indistinct, with tiny papillae and some short setae. Second pair of lobes, lateral and anterior to the ovipositor lobes, similar in size to ovipositor lobes, but bearing very long slender setae, without stout, modified ‘peg setae.’ Anterior and posterior apophyses long, stout (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 54–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1787,1812]" captionTargetBox="[161,1416,247,1681]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1431,237,1691]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54–57. Female genitalia of Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov., paratype, genitalia slide no. AD956 (MPUJ). 54, general view; 55, 56, apophyses and ovipositor; 57, coils of ductus spermathecae (broken off)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337715/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="221">Figs. 54, 56</figureCitation>
); remaining two apophyses pairs represent slender, rod-like and wide lobe-like projections called prela. Tips of one pair of rod-like prela articulating with anterior apophyses in a groove 1/2 way of their length (
<figureCitation box="[1283,1367,476,503]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1787,1812]" captionTargetBox="[161,1416,247,1681]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1431,237,1691]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54–57. Female genitalia of Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov., paratype, genitalia slide no. AD956 (MPUJ). 54, general view; 55, 56, apophyses and ovipositor; 57, coils of ductus spermathecae (broken off)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337715/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="221">Fig. 55</figureCitation>
). Vestibulum without antrum, however, vestibulum may look thickened laterally because of the prela (
<figureCitation box="[1251,1336,512,539]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1787,1812]" captionTargetBox="[161,1416,247,1681]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1431,237,1691]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54–57. Female genitalia of Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov., paratype, genitalia slide no. AD956 (MPUJ). 54, general view; 55, 56, apophyses and ovipositor; 57, coils of ductus spermathecae (broken off)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337715/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="221">Fig. 55</figureCitation>
). Ductus bursae long and very narrow (
<figureCitation box="[495,580,548,575]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1787,1812]" captionTargetBox="[161,1416,247,1681]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1431,237,1691]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54–57. Female genitalia of Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov., paratype, genitalia slide no. AD956 (MPUJ). 54, general view; 55, 56, apophyses and ovipositor; 57, coils of ductus spermathecae (broken off)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337715/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="221">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
), without pectinations. Corpus small, oval-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1165,1250,548,575]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1787,1812]" captionTargetBox="[161,1416,247,1681]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1431,237,1691]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54–57. Female genitalia of Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov., paratype, genitalia slide no. AD956 (MPUJ). 54, general view; 55, 56, apophyses and ovipositor; 57, coils of ductus spermathecae (broken off)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337715/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="221">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
), without spines or signum. Ductus spermathaecae very narrow (broken in the slide AD956, 
<figureCitation box="[1000,1082,584,611]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1787,1812]" captionTargetBox="[161,1416,247,1681]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1431,237,1691]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54–57. Female genitalia of Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov., paratype, genitalia slide no. AD956 (MPUJ). 54, general view; 55, 56, apophyses and ovipositor; 57, coils of ductus spermathecae (broken off)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337715/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="221">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
), with about 3.5 coils (
<figureCitation box="[1339,1423,584,611]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1787,1812]" captionTargetBox="[161,1416,247,1681]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1431,237,1691]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54–57. Female genitalia of Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov., paratype, genitalia slide no. AD956 (MPUJ). 54, general view; 55, 56, apophyses and ovipositor; 57, coils of ductus spermathecae (broken off)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337715/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="221">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
), utriculus absent or not preserved (
<figureCitation box="[532,616,620,647]" captionStart="FIGURES 54–57" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1787,1812]" captionTargetBox="[161,1416,247,1681]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[151,1431,237,1691]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 54–57. Female genitalia of Astrotischeria colombiana Stonis &amp; Vargas, sp. nov., paratype, genitalia slide no. AD956 (MPUJ). 54, general view; 55, 56, apophyses and ovipositor; 57, coils of ductus spermathecae (broken off)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3337715/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="221">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
